OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F438A1784832502
OL,3,CCalls for the Welsh Government to
OL,4,Cfollow England with cap on bus fares
OL,6,FIn a statement Reforms Shadow Minister
OL,7,Ffor Transport, Jason O'Connell MS
OL,8,Fsaid: "Adults in Wales are paying a
OL,9,Fhigh price for the Plaid Cymru
OL,10,FGovernment's failure to deliver a
OL,11,FWales-wide fare cap, like what is
OL,12,Fhappening over the border."
OL,14,FHe added: "Now that funding has been
OL,15,Fmade available by the UK Government,
OL,16,Fthe First Minister must act to cap bus
OL,17,Ffares and help ease the cost of living
OL,18,Ffor people across Wales."
